FT  04 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Radius sharply higher at Pounds 1.25m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Continued progress through the second six months enabled Radius, the
USM-quoted computer systems and maintenance company, to lift profits from
Pounds 366,000 to Pounds 1.23m for the year to November 30.
Rationalisation was behind a decline in turnover to Pounds 24m (Pounds 28m).
Earnings improved to 2.9p (0.8p) and a final dividend of 1.8p holds the
total at 2.7p.
