<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAR 93 / UK Company News: SR Gent ahead 47% at Pounds 986,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SR Gent, a fashion garment supplier to Marks and Spencer, achieved a 47 per
cent profits improvement to Pounds 986,000 pre-tax for the half year ended
December 31.
A fall in turnover to Pounds 59.8m (Pounds 67.8m) reflected a decision to
focus more closely on products with higher margin contribution. However,
sales were expected to recover in the second half.
Earnings rose to 1.5p (1p) and the interim dividend is held at 0.75p.
