FT  04 MAR 93 / Another executive charged by SFO
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MASON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE SERIES of prosecutions by the Serious Fraud Office over cases of alleged
corruption concerning the awarding of contracts was extended yesterday when
a marketing consultant was arrested and charged with three counts of
corruption, John Mason writes.
The charges against Mr Donald Richards, the head of Donnar Services, a
marketing company, relate to the procuring of contracts with NEI Thompson
Kennicott, a supplier of water treatment equipment to power stations. The
company is a subsidiary of Northern Engineering Industries, owned by
Rolls-Royce.
Mr Richards, of Gt Missenden, Bucks, appeared at Bow St magistrates court.
He was remanded on bail until April 15.
