<TEXT>
VENEZUELA'S President Carlos Andres Perez, speaking from a palace still
scarred by a recent coup attempt, said the country's political woes would
not turn him into a lame duck in his last months in office and he expected
Congress to approve all pending economic reforms, Reuter reports from
Caracas.
