<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Billam rises 57% to Pounds 479,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
J BILLAM, the specialist engineer, returned profits of Pounds 479,000
pre-tax for the year to end-December, an improvement of 57 per cent over the
previous Pounds 306,000.
Turnover was static at Pounds 5.99m (Pounds 5.85m) although second half
sales showed a 5 per cent rise over those for the corresponding period.
Earnings rose to 20.1p (13.3p) and a final dividend of 3.1p makes a 5p
(4.28p) total.
