FT  03 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Provident Financial obtains injunction
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Provident Financial, the consumer credit and insurance group has obtained a
high court injunction to prevent the Halifax Building Society using the name
'Halifax' in connection with motor insurance.
Provident Financial has a motor insurance subsidiary, Halifax Insurance,
specialising in private motor insurance. Provident said the injunction would
stay in force until a full hearing of the case in up to two years' time.
